Schaeuble Says Germany Wouldn’t Oppose Bringing ESM Forward

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-09-24T18:07:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/schaeuble-says-germany-wouldn-t-oppose-bringing-esm-forward.html
Germany  wouldn’t oppose a plan to
bring forward the start date for the European Stability
Mechanism, Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  said.  Speaking to reporters in  Washington , Schaeuble said he
didn’t know if it was possible to bring forward the start of the
ESM, the proposed permanent rescue plan, which is currently
slated to begin in July 2013.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Washington at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  